Jim Nwobodo on Friday made known his defection from All Progressive Congress(APC) as he re-unites with his former Political party, Peoples Democratic Party(PDP). From report gathered , Jim Nwobodo was absent from the All Pregressive Congrass(APC) presidencial campaign that took place on Thursday . He announced his defection during a visit by key leaders of the PDP in the Southeast to his Amaechi country home, in Enugu. On the entourage were S.N Okeke, former chairman, Police Service Commission, Prof. A.B.C Nwosu, Chief Oseloka Obaze, the Secretary to the Abia State Government, among others. They had asked Nwobodo to return to the PDP, a party he co-founded in 1998 